      "name": "Chhath Puja: The Supreme Solar Worship",
      "description": "Patna is the global epicenter of Chhath Puja, an ancient Vedic festival dedicated to Surya (the Sun God) and Usha (the Goddess of Dawn). Unlike other festivals, Chhath is performed at the river ghats without the mediation of priests, emphasizing a direct connection between the devotee (Vratin) and the Divine. In Patna, millions gather at the Ganga ghats to perform the ‘Arghya’ (offering of water) during sunset and sunrise. The rituals involve rigorous fasting, holy bathing, and standing in the water for long durations to honor the life-sustaining energy of the Sun. The air is filled with traditional folk melodies (Sharda Sinha’s classics), and the entire city is illuminated with handmade lamps and decorated with sugarcane stalks, representing the fertility of the Magadha soil."
